<p>I am apparently running into a Heisenbug? My goal is to test if a pointer is null. If it is, I am to create a new node in my linked list. </p>  <pre><code>printf("Before\n");     if (sumTail == 0) {         printf("After\n");         node *newHead = malloc(sizeof(node));         newHead -&gt; next = sum -&gt; head;         sum -&gt; head -&gt; prev = newHead;         sum -&gt; head = newHead;         sumTail = newHead;         newSumValue = ZERO + 1;     } else {         newSumValue = (sumTail -&gt; digit) + carry;     } </code></pre>  <p>When I run the above code, I get the following output:</p>  <pre><code>n8stewart$ ./problem  Before Segmentation fault: 11 n8stewart$  </code></pre>  <p>However, when I used lldb (I am on a mac) to debug the program, it works flawlessly with no errors. I am stuck. Why does the null pointer check result in a seg fault?</p>  <p>Thanks!</p>